        "summary": "Imam al-Sadiq (AS) entrusted Abd al-Rahman ibn Siyaba with one thousand dinars to distribute to the families of those who had been killed fighting alongside Zayd ibn Ali (AS) in his uprising against the Umayyads in 122 AH. This demonstrates the Imam's practical concern for the welfare of the martyrs' families and his tacit approval of Zayd's revolt, even though the Imam himself did not participate in it.",
